    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-12-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-12-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="379"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d379">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_CFM1">C.F.M.</gloss> Files: Lot M–88: Box 2079: <gloss
                        target="#t_CFM1">CFM</gloss> Documents</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Proposal by the <gloss type="from">United States
                            Delegation</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Council of Foreign
                            Ministers</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="54" xml:id="d379fn54">This paper was submitted by the Deputies to the
                        Council of Foreign Ministers in connection with the Deputies’ paper <gloss
                            target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM(46) (NY)</gloss>43, December 3, 1946, <ref
                            target="#pg_1396">p. 1396</ref>; for a further description of the origin
                        of this paper, see the Report of the Deputies as recorded in the United
                        States Delegation Minutes of the 14th Meeting of the Council, December 3,
                            <ref target="#pg_1382">p. 1382</ref>. After considering this paper at
                        its 14th Meeting, the Council referred it to the Trieste Sub-Committee for
                        study and recommendations; see the Record of Decisions of that Council
                        meeting, <ref target="#pg_1400">p. 1400</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM(46)(NY)</gloss>44</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-12-03">December 3,
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Peace Treaty With Italy: Free Territory of Trieste</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">Protocol of . . . . .</p>
                <p>The representatives of France, U.S.S.R., U.K., and U.S.A., assembled on . . . . .
                    at New York as the Council of Foreign Ministers, have agreed that their
                    Governments will recommend to the General <pb facs="1427" n="1403"
                        xml:id="pg_1403"/> Assembly of the United Nations during its present
                    session, the taking of the necessary steps to furnish to the Free Territory of
                    Trieste such sums as may, in the opinion of the General Assembly, be needed
                    during the first six months’ period <hi rend="italic">a</hi>) to meet the salary
                    and expenses of the Governor and any deficit in the administrative budget of the
                    Territory and <hi rend="italic">b</hi>) to make available the foreign exchange
                    resources required to meet any deficit on the Territory’s external balance of
                    payments, and will take all necessary measures to support such steps in the
                    United Nations.</p>
            </div>
